auto_merge.commit_message:
Use dict.setdefault() rather than doing the dict lookup in two steps since it
internally makes sure that nothing happens between getting and setting.
This means that all versions go through a dict pointer and not just the CPython version.
auto_merge.commit_title: Close a small thread-safety hole in runtime "cline_in_trackback" (GH-6984)

body:
Use dict setdefault rather than do the dict lookup in two steps since it internally makes sure that nothing happens between getting and settings. This means that all versions go through a dict pointer and not just the CPython version.

Optimize __Pyx_PyDict_SetDefault a little for the Limited API just because it's increasingly useful for this kind of think so we may as well try to make it as fast as possible.

comment_data.body: This uses critical sections, but was only working because the exception handling code provided the dependency
If this is only used once in the code base, why do we need to add a new option argument here rather than just changing the semantics?

comment_data.body: The `setdefault()` implementation actually fits better into `Builtins.c` by now. And it takes an unused flag argument that can be removed. I'll clean that up in master.
I've removed the extra argument. Since the dict-caching doesn't work on newer versions of Python, I don't think we're likely to add new uses for this.

commit.message:
Use dict setdefault to handle setting to False

since it internally makes sure that nothing happens between
getting and settings. This means that all versions go through
a dict pointer and not just the CPython version.

Optimize __Pyx_PyDict_SetDefault a little for the Limited API
just because it's increasingly useful for this kind of
think so we may as well try to make it fast

Fix Cython build

by adding other dependencies
